With Britons drinking less beer, Whitbread, which is trying to sell 3,000 pubs, said first-half profit slid by 16 percent, to $136 million. Whitbread, Britain's dominant operator of restaurants, fitness clubs and budget hotels, wants to sell the pubs to concentrate on its other businesses. The company, which operates Marriott hotels in Britain, is also reorganizing and rebranding parts of its restaurant division. Its shares fell slightly in London. Alan Cowell (NYT)